    "what_description": "Magnolia laevifolia is a species of flowering plant that belongs to the family Magnoliaceae. It is an evergreen tree with a broad, rounded crown and a straight, smooth trunk that can grow up to 15 meters tall. The leaves are simple, alternate, and elliptical, measuring 10-25 centimeters in length, with a leathery texture and a glabrous surface. The flowers are solitary, cup-shaped, and white, with 6-8 petals, and are borne on short, glabrous peduncles; they are hermaphroditic, with a superior ovary containing 6-8 carpels. The fruit is a follicle, measuring 5-10 centimeters in length, with 6-8 cocci.",
