    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Magnolia laevifolia are inflammation, fever is reduced by its anti-inflammatory and antipyretic properties, asthma symptoms are alleviated through its bronchodilatory effects, hypertension is lowered due to its vasodilatory action, and diarrhea is treated with its antimicrobial properties. Magnolia laevifolia's anti-inflammatory and antioxidant compounds also relieve skin irritation and cough, while its analgesic properties ease pain. Additionally, its anti-inflammatory and immunomodulatory properties help manage arthritis and digestive issues, and its anti-inflammatory and vasodilatory effects mitigate rheumatism and respiratory issues. Furthermore, Magnolia laevifolia's antidiabetic and hypoglycemic properties are beneficial for diabetes management, its anxiolytic and sedative properties are effective for anxiety, and its anti-ulcerogenic properties treat gastritis and eczema. Its anti-allergic and anti-inflammatory compounds also alleviate allergies, respiratory infection, bronchitis, and inflammatory responses.",
