    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Magnolia laevifolia are its antioxidant activity, which is attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids. This plant also exhibits antimicrobial properties, particularly against certain bacteria and fungi, thanks to the saponins present in its roots. Additionally, the anti-inflammatory properties of Magnolia laevifolia are mediated by the sesquiterpenes and alkaloids found in its bark, which can help in reducing swelling and pain. The analgesic activity of this plant is due to the volatile oils, particularly the benzyl isothiocyanate, which can inhibit the production of pain-causing chemicals in the body. Moreover, the antiviral properties of Magnolia laevifolia are attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids, which can inhibit the replication of certain viruses.",
