    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Magnolia laevifolia are magnolol, honokiol, oleanolic acid, ursolic acid, and magnolin, which have been identified as the primary bioactive compounds responsible for its therapeutic effects. Magnolol and honokiol, the main lignans present in M. laevifolia, have been shown to possess anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and anti-anxiety properties, as well as the ability to inhibit the replication of certain viruses. Oleanolic acid and ursolic acid, triterpenoid saponins present in the plant, have been found to possess anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and hepatoprotective properties, as well as the ability to inhibit the growth of certain cancer cells. Magnolin, a lignan present in M. laevifolia, has been shown to possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, as well as the ability to inhibit the replication of certain viruses. The bioactive compounds present in M. laevifolia are thought to work synergistically to produce its therapeutic effects, making it a valuable plant for the treatment of various diseases.",
