    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Magnolia laevifolia are infusion, tincture, tea, decoction, and salve. Infusion is prepared by steeping the leaves in hot water to extract flavonoids and phenolic acids, which have anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties. Tincture is made by soaking the leaves in a solvent like ethanol or glycerin to create a concentrated extract of bioactive compounds, including alkaloids and terpenoids. Decoction involves boiling the bark and roots in water to release their contained flavonoids and lignans, which are used to treat fever and respiratory issues. A salve is prepared by mixing the infused leaves with a carrier oil to create a topical application for wound healing and skin conditions.",
